Still, when I grew up, my body was changing and reacting very differently from regular to hard food intolerances; I realized that I needed something different. Frankly, seeing people eat “normal” but not me caused me to get depressed many times. As a result, I did plenty of research to find a cure and discovered unique diets which motivated me to make low-carb and gluten-free breads and desserts. Now, I see a lot of difference in my digestion and mood. So now, I am inspired to help people who do not have many options to take care of their health by eating delicious, nourishing desserts. Hence, it gives me great joy to cook those goodies with unique characteristics you can enjoy!

attributes.about_this_biz_history: In 1958, two brothers borrowed $600 from their mom to open a pizza place in Wichita, Kansas. They named it Pizza Hut because their sign only had room for eight letters. How profound! Soon, the restaurant grew. Why? The pizza was awesome. The service felt like home. And the customers were treated like family. And we've been delivering that same food and service ever since. For the Love of Pizza Since 1958. From day one, the Carney brothers could look their customers in the eye and promise them the finest pizza in town -- because they knew the farmers who grew the ingredients, and they knew those farmers cared about quality. Since then, our farmers have grown right alongside us, and the ingredients we use are still our highest priority. No one loves pizza more than Pizza Hut. That's why pizza is in our name -- and always will be.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Owner / Manager / Executive Chef, Parinya, has been cooking Thai food from a very young age when she preapared meals for her family in Thailand and sold hot food on the street in front of her house. She has a passion and talent for Thai food, arts and culture and enjoyed sharing this with her friends and family. And now, she is able to share this passion with her customers at Ban Chok Dee Thai Cuisine. She can be seen running between the kitchen and the customers to make sure everything is just right!

She enjoys cooking, fruit and vegetable carving, decorating and flower arrangements, and loves to share these skills with others, whether it is through the dining experience at the restaurant; catering for a wedding or party; or directly through the cooking and carving classes that she offers.

In addition to Parinya, our current chefs all bring many years of experience cooking in the restaurants of Thailand and share Parinya's passion for food.
attributes.about_this_biz_history:
Ban Chok Dee Thai Cuisine opened in the summer of 2009 and is locally owned and operated. The owner, Parinya, moved to Canada from Thailand in 1998 and is committed to providing authentic, great tasting Thai food with traditional & friendly Thai service.

Starting out on 203 Street in Langley with 5 staff, we moved to our current location on Douglas Crescent in the summer of 2012 and now have around 15 employees and seating for up to 120 guests.

We have been voted one of the Best Thai Restaurants in Langley since 2011 by the readers of the Langley Advance, and we are currently the only restaurant in Langley to have been awarded the Thai Select designation which is determined by the Thailand Department of International Trade Promotion.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
We offer authentic Thai cuisine in a casual fine dining experience with a warm and relaxing atmosphere. Our award winning cuisine is a source of pride for our staff, and every dish is prepared to order for the individual taste of our valued customers.

We offer vegetarian, gluten-free & allergy substitutions on nearly everything on the menu. We are a licensed premesis with a wide selection of beverages, including wine, import & domestic beer, liquor and specialty coffees & teas. We also offer off-site catering for weddings & parties; group specials for dine-in and take-out; as well as our popular hands-on Thai Cooking and Carving Classes.

Our dedication ensures that you absorb not only the true essence of Greek life, its food, its wine and its culture, but of equal importance, the very passion of the Greek people themselves. Our cuisine is authentically cooked or prepared on our charcoal brazier.

Owner / Manager / Executive Chef, Parinya, has been cooking Thai food from a very young age when she preapared meals for her family in Thailand and sold hot food on the street in front of her house. She has a passion and talent for Thai food, arts and culture and enjoyed sharing this with her friends and family. And now, she is able to share this passion with her customers at Ban Chok Dee Thai Cuisine. She can be seen running between the kitchen and the customers to make sure everything is just right!

She enjoys cooking, fruit and vegetable carving, decorating and flower arrangements, and loves to share these skills with others, whether it is through the dining experience at the restaurant; catering for a wedding or party; or directly through the cooking and carving classes that she offers.

In addition to Parinya, our current chefs all bring many years of experience cooking in the restaurants of Thailand and share Parinya's passion for food.

We have been voted one of the Best Thai Restaurants in Langley since 2011 by the readers of the Langley Advance, and we are currently the only restaurant in Langley to have been awarded the Thai Select designation which is determined by the Thailand Department of International Trade Promotion.

attributes.about_this_biz_history: In 1958, two brothers borrowed $600 from their mom to open a pizza place in Wichita, Kansas. They named it Pizza Hut because their sign only had room for eight letters. How profound! Soon, the restaurant grew. Why? The pizza was awesome. The service felt like home. And the customers were treated like family. And we've been delivering that same food and service ever since. For the Love of Pizza Since 1958. From day one, the Carney brothers could look their customers in the eye and promise them the finest pizza in town -- because they knew the farmers who grew the ingredients, and they knew those farmers cared about quality. Since then, our farmers have grown right alongside us, and the ingredients we use are still our highest priority. No one loves pizza more than Pizza Hut. That's why pizza is in our name -- and always will be.
